	- global variables can be made local (private) with closures
	- global and local variables with the same name are different variables
		- modifying one, does not modify the other
	- JavaScript variables created without a declaration keyword (var, let, or const) are always global, even if they are created inside a function
	- local are created when the function is invoked, and deleted when the function is finished
	- all functions have access to the global scope
	- all functions have access to the scope above them
