- infos/ecosystem/background
	- using buildSchema is generally inadvisable, as it severely limits the functionality of your schema ([source](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/53984094/notable-differences-between-buildschema-and-graphqlschema))
		- cannot specify resolve functions for individual fields
		- cannot specify either resolveType or isTypeOf properties for Types, making it impossible to use Unions and Interfaces
		- cannot utilize custom scalars
	- How to query all the GraphQL type fields without writing a long query?
		- Unfortunately what you'd like to do is not possible. GraphQL requires you to be explicit about specifying which fields you would like returned from your query.
		- Ok, and if I request some object of an unknown form from backend which I'm supposed to proxy or send back?
		- the whole idea of graphql is that there is no such thing as an "unkown form". 
		- interesting, it really is a different mindset when using graphql 
