- React Router 6.4 was released in September 2022
	- new features
		- watched: [React Router 6.4 Release Preview](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aX74DbFT5nI)
			- Data API extracted from Remix
				- Remix is created by Ryan Florence and Michael Jackson, the creators of React Router
			- nearly every route need to fetch data
				- React Router will call data fetches in parallel before the route is rendered
				- then access the data with the useLoaderData hook
			- only the data of the changing routes is loaded
			- has 404 pages
			- point a form action at a route, and add a route action
				- it works like server actions in Next.js but the examples are obviously client-side React
			- has optimistic UI
				- the expected value is displayed and will only change if another value is fetched
			- *"It's hard to explain just how much simpler and more capable your code becomes when your router understands the full data lifecycle with data loading and mutations."*
